Package: robustness
Type: Package
Title: Range Tests for Equality and Equivalence Across Specifications
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("David A.", "Jaeger", email = "david.jaeger@st-andrews.ac.uk",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Computes range-based and Wald-based tests of equality and
    equivalence across a set of model specifications, from saved bootstrap
    draws of a coefficient of interest. Given the full-sample estimates and a
    matrix of uncentred bootstrap draws, the package reports the observed
    range and Wald statistics, equivalence bounds at chosen significance
    levels, and bootstrap p-values for the equality tests. It implements the
    method of Jaeger (2026) and is the R counterpart of the Stata 'robustness'
    command; given the same draws the two produce the same statistics. The
    package computes statistics from draws and does not generate the draws.
